<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="309" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
The 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group was proposed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Esben-Petersen, P" journalOrPublisher="Entomotaxonomia" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" refId="B11" refString="Esben-Petersen, P, 1921. Mecoptera. Monographic revision: Collections zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps. Catalogue systematique et descriptif 5: 1-172." title="Mecoptera. Monographic revision: Collections zoologiques du Baron Edm. de Selys Longchamps. Catalogue systematique et descriptif 5: 1 - 172." year="1921">Esben-Petersen (1921)</bibRefCitation>
to contain 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. sibirica" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Martynova, OM" journalOrPublisher="Entomologischeskoe Obozreni" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="721 - 747" refId="B30" refString="Martynova, OM, 1957. Skorpionnitzy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR II. Semejstvo Panorpidae. Entomologischeskoe Obozreni 36: 721 - 747" title="Skorpionnitzy (Mecoptera) fauny SSSR II. Semejstvo Panorpidae." volume="36" year="1957">Martynova (1957)</bibRefCitation>
later transferred 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. sibirica" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="sibirica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. sibirica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the 
<taxonomicName genus="Р." lsidName="Р. communis" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="communis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">
<normalizedToken originalValue="Р">R</normalizedToken>
. communis
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Carpenter, FM" journalOrPublisher="Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="267 - 281" refId="B7" refString="Carpenter, FM, 1938. Mecoptera from China, with descriptions of new species. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington 40: 267 - 281" title="Mecoptera from China, with descriptions of new species." volume="40" year="1938">Carpenter (1938)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng, FY" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="1 - 117" refId="B9" refString="Cheng, FY, 1957. Revision of the Chinese Mecoptera. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 116: 1 - 117" title="Revision of the Chinese Mecoptera." volume="116" year="1957">Cheng (1957)</bibRefCitation>
, this species group consisted of 19 Chinese species of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without anal horn on the posterior margin of T6 in males. Of these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Navas" authorityYear="1931" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Panorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Panorpa tincta" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tincta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Panorpa tincta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<normalizedToken originalValue="Navás">Navas</normalizedToken>
, 1931 was transferred to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cai &amp; Hua" authorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Panorpidae" genus="Sinopanorpa" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sinopanorpa" order="Mecoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">Sinopanorpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" author="Cai, LJ" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" pagination="43 - 54" refId="B5" refString="Cai, LJ, Huang, PY, Hua, BZ, 2008. Sinopanorpa, a new genus of Panorpidae (Mecoptera) from the Oriental China with descriptions of two new species. Zootaxa 1941: 43 - 54, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" title="Sinopanorpa, a new genus of Panorpidae (Mecoptera) from the Oriental China with descriptions of two new species." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.1941.1.4" volume="1941" year="2008">Cai et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and 12 species that differ remarkably from 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are herein removed from this group. In this paper, 21 species are recognized in the newly defined 
<taxonomicName genus="P." lsidName="P. davidi" pageId="0" pageNumber="309" rank="species" species="davidi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="309">P. davidi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, including 17 known species and four new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
